==What do all those buttons do?==
The buttons are self-explanatory. From left to right:
:*[[File:en/Manual/Build rail.png]] '''Build Track''': (first four buttons): Builds track in the selected direction, you can click and drag for non-diagonal tracks.
:*[[File:en/Manual/Build autorail.png]] '''Autorail Button''': (shortcut A): Click and drag, can also be used to build diagonal tracks (probably needs a better explanation).
:*[[File:en/Manual/Clear title.png]] '''[[en/Clear Tile]] Button'''
:*[[File:en/Manual/Lower land.png]] '''[[en/Lower Land]] Button'''
:*[[File:en/Manual/Raise land.png]] '''[[en/Raise Land]] Button'''
:*[[File:en/Manual/Build traindepot.png]] '''Build [[en/Manual/Depots]] Button''': Opens the depot build window for you to select a depot direction to build.
